{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/webauthn/part-4-making-auth-better/","webpackCompilationHash":"81dda3e49541104d54c7","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Six of one","author":"Ben Lowry"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"13a2f7c2-3848-5493-bf9c-b7e3796c5715","excerpt":"Other posts in this series: Forget your passwords with the Web Authentication API The problem with passwords The Web Authentication API How can WebAuthn be‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Other posts in this series:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"../part-1-forget-your-passwords\">Forget your passwords with the Web Authentication API</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"../part-2-the-problem-with-passwords\">The problem with passwords</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"../part-3-web-authentication-api\">The Web Authentication API</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>How can WebAuthn be better for users?</h2>\n<p>Allowing a user to create an account without a password means\ntheir account is less likely to be compromised,\nand the use of more secure (when compared to SMS),\nand easier-to-use 2FA (when compared to one time passcodes).\nThose should do the trick!</p>\n<p>You can <a href=\"https://webauth.io\">try it out for yourself</a> if you have an authenticator\n(remember: if you‚Äôre using a phone there‚Äôs a good chance you‚Äôre holding one).\nIf you don‚Äôt have an authenticator, I‚Äôve recorded a video showing how easy it is to register and login.</p>\n<video width=\"630\" controls style=\"max-width: 100%;\">\n  <source src=\"/af29446d2127747f7b276eb881fe67d8/register-login-demo.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">\nYour browser does not support the video tag.\n</video>\n<br />\nThat all looks good, but there might be a few other things you need to consider.\n<h2>How do I enable WebAuthn for my users?</h2>\n<p>Ultimately, a lot of these decisions are up to you/your company to decide,\nbut I‚Äôll give my thoughts below as well. Here are some things to think about:</p>\n<p>üößüë∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Still working on this bit üë∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èüöß</p>\n<h3>Registration</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Passwordless login or second factor?</li>\n<li>Is a password still required?</li>\n<li>Is a password still <em>allowed</em>?</li>\n<li>Register the token now or later?</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How do you make the feature discoverable?</h3>\n<p>How do you get more people using it?\n‚Ä¢ Hints on the login page?\n‚Ä¢ Prompt after logging in with password? <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/1e7ecbc9d6d0e0a8453c4e5c28fdca59/df67e/ux-prompt.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 85.12820512820514%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Prompt that the ability to use a platform authenticator is available to help users discover\" title=\"Prompt that the ability to use a platform authenticator is available to help users discover\" src=\"/static/1e7ecbc9d6d0e0a8453c4e5c28fdca59/b9e4f/ux-prompt.png\" srcset=\"/static/1e7ecbc9d6d0e0a8453c4e5c28fdca59/cf440/ux-prompt.png 148w,\n/static/1e7ecbc9d6d0e0a8453c4e5c28fdca59/d2d38/ux-prompt.png 295w,\n/static/1e7ecbc9d6d0e0a8453c4e5c28fdca59/b9e4f/ux-prompt.png 590w,\n/static/1e7ecbc9d6d0e0a8453c4e5c28fdca59/f9b6a/ux-prompt.png 885w,\n/static/1e7ecbc9d6d0e0a8453c4e5c28fdca59/df67e/ux-prompt.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n‚Ä¢ What kind of messages do you want?\n‚Ä¢ How forcefully will you push?</p>\n<h3>Login</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Passwordless? Do you have a different login page entirely or a separate form?</li>\n<li>Usernameless? More conditions to meet, but it‚Äôs an option</li>\n<li>Fall back to using a password?</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/65ce0d8d84bddabd4f38585f85fbaad0/8d582/ux-log-in.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 93.66391184573003%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Log in page with username and password fields\" title=\"Log in page with username and password fields\" src=\"/static/65ce0d8d84bddabd4f38585f85fbaad0/b9e4f/ux-log-in.png\" srcset=\"/static/65ce0d8d84bddabd4f38585f85fbaad0/cf440/ux-log-in.png 148w,\n/static/65ce0d8d84bddabd4f38585f85fbaad0/d2d38/ux-log-in.png 295w,\n/static/65ce0d8d84bddabd4f38585f85fbaad0/b9e4f/ux-log-in.png 590w,\n/static/65ce0d8d84bddabd4f38585f85fbaad0/8d582/ux-log-in.png 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<h3>Account management</h3>\n<p>Manage devices:</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/2afcc/ux-creds.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 26.148969889064976%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Manage devices page to allow adding a device\" title=\"Manage devices page to allow adding a device\" src=\"/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/b9e4f/ux-creds.png\" srcset=\"/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/cf440/ux-creds.png 148w,\n/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/d2d38/ux-creds.png 295w,\n/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/b9e4f/ux-creds.png 590w,\n/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/f9b6a/ux-creds.png 885w,\n/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/2d849/ux-creds.png 1180w,\n/static/ca8e9303a9134a209c6c67d84bda1f5f/2afcc/ux-creds.png 1262w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<ul>\n<li>Nicknames</li>\n<li>Last used</li>\n<li>Prompt to (or automatically) remove ‚Äúold‚Äù authentication methods</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/1ebe0/ux-unused.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 17.539863325740317%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Manage devices page with prompt for unused device\" title=\"Manage devices page with prompt for unused device\" src=\"/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/b9e4f/ux-unused.png\" srcset=\"/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/cf440/ux-unused.png 148w,\n/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/d2d38/ux-unused.png 295w,\n/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/b9e4f/ux-unused.png 590w,\n/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/f9b6a/ux-unused.png 885w,\n/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/2d849/ux-unused.png 1180w,\n/static/4202ad088750a450236990c2a37c37dd/1ebe0/ux-unused.png 1756w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<h3>Account recovery</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Password or no?</li>\n<li>Magic link <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/11824ebe78fec2971accc07ba4310cc1/00212/ux-magic-link.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 83.95604395604394%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Allow login with a magic link or OTP\" title=\"Allow login with a magic link or OTP\" src=\"/static/11824ebe78fec2971accc07ba4310cc1/b9e4f/ux-magic-link.png\" srcset=\"/static/11824ebe78fec2971accc07ba4310cc1/cf440/ux-magic-link.png 148w,\n/static/11824ebe78fec2971accc07ba4310cc1/d2d38/ux-magic-link.png 295w,\n/static/11824ebe78fec2971accc07ba4310cc1/b9e4f/ux-magic-link.png 590w,\n/static/11824ebe78fec2971accc07ba4310cc1/f9b6a/ux-magic-link.png 885w,\n/static/11824ebe78fec2971accc07ba4310cc1/00212/ux-magic-link.png 910w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span></li>\n<li>Store their email. VERIFY</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>What have the big companies done/who can I copy?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Twitter ‚Äî single key</li>\n<li>Microsoft ‚Äî many keys</li>\n<li>Facebook ‚Äî many keys</li>\n<li>Google ‚Äî many keys</li>\n<li>GitHub ‚Äî single key?</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Making auth better","date":"January 26, 2020","description":"How do you actually go about adding WebAuthn to your site or application? In the fourth post in the WebAuthn series, we'll explore some options"},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"3 min read"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/webauthn/part-4-making-auth-better/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/webauthn/part-3-web-authentication-api/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The Web Authentication API"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/fsm-all-stages/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using Finite State Machines to build better software"}}}}}